    <h1>Different types of Hamster Breeds</h1>
       <h2>Syrian Hamster</h2>
	     <img src="images/syrianham.jpeg" alt="Grey Syrian Hamster">
         <p>Traits: unsociable, calm, nocturnal,likes to be alone </p>
         <p>Average lifespan: 2-3 years</p>
	     <p>Average size: around 3-4 inches</p>
       
      <h2>Chinese Hamster</h2>
	     <img src="images/chinesehamster.jpg" alt="Chinese Hamster">
         <p>Traits: quick,playful,high maintenance,hyperactive</p>
	     <p>Average lifespan: 2-3 years</p>
	     <p>Average size: 3-4 inches 
	  
	  <h2>Roborovski Hamster</h2>
	    <img src="images/roboham.jpg" alt="A tiny Robo Hamster">
	     <p>Traits: sociable, fast, selfish, independent, like to live with other hamsters 
	     <p>Average lifespan:2.5-3 years 
	     <p>Average size: 2 inches </p>
	     
	  <h2>Cambell Russian Hamster </h2>
	     <img src="images/campbellham.jpg" alt="A Dark Grey Campbell">
	     <p> Traits: shy, affectionate, likes extremely quiet places, like hiding </p>
	     <p>Average lifespan: 1.5-2 years </p>
	     <p>Average size: 2-4 years </p>
	    
	  <h2>Hamster housing</h2>
	   <ul>
	    <li>All species of hamsters like big and spacious environment. Wired cages are bad. A big plastic container is better.</li>
	    <li>Containers should be atleast 24 inches by 12 inches. </li>
	    <li>Lots of places to hide is recommended. With fresh food and water daily.</li>
	    <li>Quiet and secluded spaces are ideal to place cages </li>
	    </ul>
	   
